
<!--Badge is Fixed to Top-Left of Page -->
<div id="badge-container" class="hidden-xs">
  <a id="badge-link" href="#page-header"> <span id="th-badge" class=""> TH </span> </a>
</div>

<header id="page-header" class="bgimage landing-header">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="halfway-down">
      <h1>TripHappy</h1>
      <h3>A better way to explore the world. Coming soon.</h3>

      <form class="form-inline">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="sr-only" for="inputEmail1">E-mail</label>
          <input class="form-lg" id="inputEmail1" type="text" placeHolder="Enter Your E-mail" />
        </div>
        <input type="submit" class="btn btn-success btn-lg" id="submitEmail1" value="Tell Me When It's Ready" />
      </form>

    </div> <!-- End Halfway Down -->
  </div> <!-- End Container -->
</header>

<div class="teaser" id="feature-teaser">
  <a href="#feature-teaser" class="">
    <p class="center-block">Tell Me More<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-down center-block"> </span></p>
  </a>
</div>

<section id="pitch" class="">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h2 class="">Discover, Plan, and Book Amazing Trips Around the World</h2>
      </div>

      <div id="sub-pitch" class="col-lg-12">
        <p>Trip Happy makes multi-city trip planning easy by bringing together dozens of travel resources onto one site - no need for hundreds of bookmarks or that 300 page guide book.  Our custom tools deliver the best travel recommendations and most up-to-date information directly to you. Trip Happy has all the information you need for each stage of your trip. Planning a trip has never been easier.</p>
      </div>

      <section class="col-sm-4 feature-block">
        <h3>Find Your Paradise</h3>
        <%= image_tag("paradise-feature-sm.jpg", :alt => "Get Tips from Other Travelers", :class => "img-rounded img-responsive center-block") %>
        <p class="text-justify">The best recommendations always come from other travelers. Browse community created trips to countries all across the globe and discover your next travel destination.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="col-sm-4 feature-block">
        <h3>Visualize Your Trip</h3>
        <%= image_tag("map-feature-sm.jpg", :alt => "Discover Your Paradise", :class => "img-rounded img-responsive center-block") %>
        <p class="text-justify">Our interactive travel planner makes it easy to link multiple cities into a personalized travel map. Share your map with others or embed it on your blog.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="col-sm-4 feature-block">
        <h3>Go Anywhere. From Anywhere.</h3>
        <%= image_tag("schedule-feature-sm.jpeg", :alt => "Step-by-step directions to anywhere in the world", :class => "img-rounded img-responsive center-block") %>
        <p class="text-justify">Get step-by-step directions to anywhere in the world. Find detailed plane, train, bus, and ferry schedules on over 800,000 routes worldwide.</p>
      </section>

    </div> <!-- End Pitch Row -->
  </div> <!-- End Pitch Container -->
</section> <!-- End Pitch Section -->

<div class="teaser" id="countdown-teaser">
  <a href="#countdown-teaser">
    <p class="center-block">So When Can I Start?<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-down center-block"></span></p>
  </a>
</div>

<section id="countdown" class="valign-middle-parent">
  <div class="container valign-middle-child" id="countdown-content">
    <div class="row">

      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h2>Assuming Our Chinese Wi-Fi Holds Up, We Will Launch In:</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="digits"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-12" id="digits-label">
        <span>days</span>
        <span>hours</span>
        <span>minutes</span>
        <span>seconds</span>
      </div>


      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h3>Give us your e-mail and we'll send you an invite to beta when it's ready.</h3>
        <form class="form-inline">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label class="sr-only" for="inputEmail2">E-mail</label>
            <input class="form-lg" id="inputEmail2" type="text" placeHolder="E-mail Address" />
          </div>
          <input type="submit" class="btn btn-success btn-lg" id="submitEmail2" value="Sounds Good" />
        </form>
      </div>

    </div> <!-- End Countdown Row -->
  </div> <!-- End Countdown Container -->
</section> <!-- End Countdown Section -->

<div class="teaser" id="about-teaser">
  <a href="#about-teaser">
    <p class="center-block">Wait, Chinese Wi-Fi?<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-down center-block"></span></p>
  </a>
</div>

<section id="about">
  <div id="about-content" class="container text-center">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h2>The Perfect Travel Tool. Built by Travelers.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <p class="text-muted text-left">
          The ideal trip planner can only be built by real travelers, so we decided to pack our lives into suitcases and hop on a flight. TripHappy will be completely built while on the road, from guesthouses, AirBnb's and coffee shops along the way (you can follow our progress on the map below). We know what it takes to plan a once-in-a-lifetime trip, and we want to help you create your own.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Our Google Travel Map -->
      <div id="google-maps">
        <iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zrDvaBECWZxs.krbN8QY-_KOk" width="640" height="330"></iframe>
      </div>

      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <p class="text-muted text-left">
          While there is an endless supply of information online for the most popular tourist sites, it is almost impossible to plan a visit to more off-the-beaten-path destinations. As a result, many travelers miss out on amazing experiences. We are tired of using out of date guide books and endless Google searching to create unique itineraries - now there is a better way.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div> <!-- End About Row -->
  </div> <!-- End About Container -->
</section> <!-- End About Section -->

